juniTsmMIB.name: juniTsmMIB

revisions.description: Changed enum names for juniTsmPortType: from 'generalPurposeDedicated' to 'generalPurposeStatic' and from 'scurityDedicated' to 'securityStatic' and added enum 'securityDynamic'. Expanded range of juniTsmPortProvisionedInterfaces.
Initial version of this MIB module.

juniTsmMIB.contactinfo: Juniper Networks, Inc. Postal: 10 Technology Park Drive Westford, MA 01886-3146 USA Tel: +1 978 589 5800 Email: mib@Juniper.net
juniTsmMIB.description: The Tunnel Server Management (TSM) MIB for the Juniper Networks enterprise.

JuniTsmLocationType.name: JuniTsmLocationType
JuniTsmLocationType.description: Describes the platform-dependent interpretation of a JuniTsmLocationValue object: unknown Unspecified/unknown slotPort Two octets in length; first octet is 'slot', second octet is 'port' slotAdapterPort Three octets in length; first octet is 'slot', second octet is 'adapter', third octet is 'port' adapterPort Two octets in length; first octet is 'adapter', second octet is 'port'

JuniTsmLocationValue.name: JuniTsmLocationValue
JuniTsmLocationValue.description: The value of a platform-dependent interface location, represented as an OCTET STRING. A corresponding JuniTsmLocationType object will identify the mapping of octets to location elements, e.g. 'slot.port'. Note, when the value of an object having this syntax is encoded as a MIB table INDEX, the rules for encoding a variable-length OCTET STRING are observed.

juniTsmLocationType.name: juniTsmLocationType
juniTsmLocationType.description: Describes the interpretation of JuniTsmLocationValue object values into platform-dependent interface location components, e.g., 'slot.port'.

juniTsmPortTable.name: juniTsmPortTable
juniTsmPortTable.description: This table allows dynamic server ports to be configured and also provides information about static ports available in the system. This table represents all ports known to the system. The presence of a port in this table does not guarantee that a card with this port is present in the chassis.

juniTsmPortLocation.name: juniTsmPortLocation
juniTsmPortLocation.description: The value of a port location.

juniTsmPortType.name: juniTsmPortType
juniTsmPortType.description: The port type: generalPurposeStatic - statically configured (always on) port, generalPurposeDynamic - dynamic port, which could be both configured with different maximum number of interfaces and unconfigured, securityStatic - static port equipped with encryption (IPSEC) hardware. securityDynamic - dynamic port with encryption (IPSEC) hardware, which could be both configured with different maximum number of interfaces and unconfigured.

juniTsmPortAvailableInterfaces.name: juniTsmPortAvailableInterfaces
juniTsmPortAvailableInterfaces.description: Maximum number of interfaces available on the port.

juniTsmPortProvisionedInterfaces.name: juniTsmPortProvisionedInterfaces
juniTsmPortProvisionedInterfaces.description: Number of interfaces provisioned on the port. '-1' means all available interfaces. If port is static this value cannot be changed. If the number of provisioned interfaces is decreased it may require a lengthy 'draining' process to bring number of allocated interfaces into compliance.

juniTsmAppRegistryTable.name: juniTsmAppRegistryTable
juniTsmAppRegistryTable.description: This table describes currently registered applications.

juniTsmAppRegistryIndex.name: juniTsmAppRegistryIndex
juniTsmAppRegistryIndex.description: A small integer identifying registered application. Once an application is registered, this integer will be associated with the application until the next reboot.

juniTsmAppRegistryIfType.name: juniTsmAppRegistryIfType
juniTsmAppRegistryIfType.description: Interface type associated with the application.

juniTsmAppRegistryName.name: juniTsmAppRegistryName
juniTsmAppRegistryName.description: The name of the application used by the system.

juniTsmAppRegistryInterfaceLimit.name: juniTsmAppRegistryInterfaceLimit
juniTsmAppRegistryInterfaceLimit.description: The maximum number of interfaces per port this application supports. (The number of interfaces could be further limited by the port capacity.)

juniTsmApplicationTable.name: juniTsmApplicationTable
juniTsmApplicationTable.description: The entries in this table describe application load on tunnel servers. This table includes only applications which are actually being used.

juniTsmApplicationMaxInterfaces.name: juniTsmApplicationMaxInterfaces
juniTsmApplicationMaxInterfaces.description: Maximum number of interfaces available on the port for the application. Applications allocate interfaces from a common pool, so this is not the only limit of application level interfaces. This value could be greater than juniTsmPortProvisionedInterfaces when the port is draining interfaces.

juniTsmApplicationActiveInterfaces.name: juniTsmApplicationActiveInterfaces
juniTsmApplicationActiveInterfaces.description: Number of application interfaces in use on the port. This value could be greater than juniTsmPortProvisionedInterfaces when the port is draining interfaces.

juniTsmCompliance.name: juniTsmCompliance
juniTsmCompliance.description: The compliance statement for TSM mib.

juniTsmGroup.name: juniTsmGroup
juniTsmGroup.description: A collection of objects providing management of TSM functionality in a Juniper product.
